Ask HN: How can I can side money with my engineering skills?
text:
Many nights outside of work, I still read and build ideas that get me excited about tech. As time grows, it would be nice to make some money on the side with the skills I have. How can I work toward this goal?

I'm a senior engineer at a large bay area tech company working in backend/distributed systems. I have experience with UI/UX as well (which I really love to do for fun!).

I started a Youtube channel and get a few hundred bucks a month from that, but am interested in building some stuff outside of videos/teaching.

title: Ask HN: What are some good fully work from anywhere companies?
text:
By good fully work from anywhere companies I mean: Safetywing, Supabase, Convertkit, Automattic, etc.

I am building my academic research around fully distributed teams and also building a job board for such jobs at the same time.

The common issue I see is that most companies that says work from anywhere are not truly work from anywhere, they restrict based on location/timezone. So, it's harder to spot fully worldwide remote companies.

There are dozens of problems when it comes to international hiring/ work from anywhere. So, not all companies can do that. I understand that.

I need your help to identify some best work from anywhere companies for my study. Please let me know if you know any.
